trans-unit.source: Add support for add-in commands for Outlook Mobile
trans-unit.target: Agregar compatibilidad a los comandos de complemento para Outlook Mobile

trans-unit.source: **Note**: Add-in commands for Outlook Mobile are currently only supported by Outlook for iOS.
trans-unit.target: **Nota**: Los comandos de complemento para Outlook Mobile solo se admiten en estos momentos en Outlook para iOS.

trans-unit.source: Using add-in commands in Outlook Mobile allows your users to access the same functionality (with some [limitations](#code-considerations)) that they already have in Outlook for Windows, Outlook for Mac, and Outlook on the web. Adding support for Outlook Mobile requires updating the add-in manifest and possibly changing your code for mobile scenarios.
trans-unit.target: Usar comandos de complemento en Outlook Mobile permite que los usuarios tengan acceso a las mismas funciones (con algunas [limitaciones](#code-considerations)) que ya tienen en Outlook para Windows, Outlook para Mac y Outlook en la web. Para agregar compatibilidad para Outlook Mobile se necesita actualizar el manifiesto del complemento y, posiblemente, cambiar el código de los escenarios móviles.

trans-unit.source: Using add-in commands in Outlook Mobile allows your users to access the same functionality (with some [limitations](#code-considerations)) that they already have in Outlook for Windows, Outlook for Mac, and Outlook on the web.
trans-unit.target: Using add-in commands in Outlook Mobile allows your users to access the same functionality (with some [limitations](#code-considerations)) that they already have in Outlook for Windows, Outlook for Mac, and Outlook on the web.

trans-unit.source: Adding support for Outlook Mobile requires updating the add-in manifest and possibly changing your code for mobile scenarios.
trans-unit.target: Adding support for Outlook Mobile requires updating the add-in manifest and possibly changing your code for mobile scenarios.

trans-unit.source: Updating the manifest
trans-unit.target: Actualizar el manifiesto

trans-unit.source: The first step to enabling add-in commands in Outlook Mobile is to define them in the add-in manifest. The **VersionOverrides** v1.1 schema defines a new form factor for mobile, [MobileFormFactor](../../reference/manifest/mobileformfactor.md).
trans-unit.target: El primer paso para habilitar los comandos de complemento en Outlook Mobile es definirlos en el manifiesto del complemento. El esquema **VersionOverrides** v1.1 define un nuevo factor de forma para dispositivos móviles, [MobileFormFactor](../../reference/manifest/mobileformfactor.md).

trans-unit.source: The first step to enabling add-in commands in Outlook Mobile is to define them in the add-in manifest.
trans-unit.target: The first step to enabling add-in commands in Outlook Mobile is to define them in the add-in manifest.

trans-unit.source: The **VersionOverrides** v1.1 schema defines a new form factor for mobile, [MobileFormFactor](../../reference/manifest/mobileformfactor.md).
trans-unit.target: The **VersionOverrides** v1.1 schema defines a new form factor for mobile, [MobileFormFactor](../../reference/manifest/mobileformfactor.md).

trans-unit.source: This element contains all of the information for loading the add-in in mobile clients. This enables you to define completely different UI elements and JavaScript files for the mobile experience.
trans-unit.target: Este elemento contiene toda la información para cargar el complemento en clientes móviles. Esto le permite definir completamente diferentes elementos de interfaz de usuario y archivos de JavaScript para la experiencia móvil.

trans-unit.source: This element contains all of the information for loading the add-in in mobile clients.
trans-unit.target: This element contains all of the information for loading the add-in in mobile clients.

trans-unit.source: This enables you to define completely different UI elements and JavaScript files for the mobile experience.
trans-unit.target: This enables you to define completely different UI elements and JavaScript files for the mobile experience.

trans-unit.source: The following example shows a single taskpane button in a **MobileFormFactor** element.
trans-unit.target: En el siguiente ejemplo se muestra un único botón del panel de tareas en un elemento **MobileFormFactor**.

trans-unit.source: This is very similar to the elements that appear in a [DesktopFormFactor](../../reference/manifest/desktopformfactor.md) element, with some notable differences.
trans-unit.target: Esto es muy similar a los elementos que aparecen en un elemento [DesktopFormFactor](../../reference/manifest/desktopformfactor.md), con algunas diferencias notables.

trans-unit.source: The [OfficeTab](../../reference/manifest/officetab.md) element is not used.
trans-unit.target: El elemento [OfficeTab](../../reference/manifest/officetab.md) no se usa.

trans-unit.source: The [ExtensionPoint](../../reference/manifest/exensionpoint.md) element must have only one child element. If the add-in only adds one button, the child element should be a [Control](../../reference/manifest/control.md) element. If the add-in adds more than one button, the child element should be a [Group](../../reference/manifest/group.md) element that contains multiple `Control` elements.
trans-unit.target: El elemento [ExtensionPoint](../../reference/manifest/exensionpoint.md) solo debe tener un elemento secundario. Si el complemento solo agrega un botón, el elemento secundario debe ser un elemento [Control](../../reference/manifest/control.md). Si el complemento agrega más de un botón, el elemento secundario debe ser un elemento [Group](../../reference/manifest/group.md) que contenga varios elementos `Control`.

trans-unit.source: The [ExtensionPoint](../../reference/manifest/exensionpoint.md) element must have only one child element.
trans-unit.target: The [ExtensionPoint](../../reference/manifest/exensionpoint.md) element must have only one child element.

trans-unit.source: If the add-in only adds one button, the child element should be a [Control](../../reference/manifest/control.md) element.
trans-unit.target: If the add-in only adds one button, the child element should be a [Control](../../reference/manifest/control.md) element.

trans-unit.source: If the add-in adds more than one button, the child element should be a [Group](../../reference/manifest/group.md) element that contains multiple `Control` elements.
trans-unit.target: If the add-in adds more than one button, the child element should be a [Group](../../reference/manifest/group.md) element that contains multiple `Control` elements.

trans-unit.source: There is no `Menu` type equivalent for the `Control` element.
trans-unit.target: No existe ningún tipo `Menu` equivalente para el elemento `Control`.

trans-unit.source: The [Supertip](../../reference/manifest/supertip.md) element is not used.

trans-unit.source: The required icon sizes are different. Mobile add-ins minimally must support 25x25, 32x32 and 48x48 pixel icons.
trans-unit.target: Los tamaños de icono necesarios son diferentes. Los complementos móviles deben admitir mínimamente iconos de 25x25, 32x32 y 48x48 píxeles.

trans-unit.source: Code considerations
trans-unit.target: Consideraciones de código

trans-unit.source: Designing an add-in for mobile introduces some additional considerations.
trans-unit.target: Diseñar un complemento para dispositivos móviles presenta algunas consideraciones adicionales.

trans-unit.source: Use REST instead of Exchange Web Services
trans-unit.target: Usar REST en lugar de servicios Web Exchange

trans-unit.source: The [Office.context.mailbox.makeEwsRequestAsync](../../reference/outlook/Office.context.mailbox.md) method is not supported in Outlook Mobile. Add-ins should prefer to get information from the Office.js API when possible. If add-ins require information not exposed by the Office.js API, then they should use the [Outlook REST APIs](https://dev.outlook.com/restapi/reference) to access the user's mailbox.
trans-unit.target: El método [Office.context.mailbox.makeEwsRequestAsync](../../reference/outlook/Office.context.mailbox.md) no se admite en Outlook Mobile. Los complementos deben preferir obtener información de la API de Office.js siempre que sea posible. Si los complementos necesitan información que no expone la API de Office.js, entonces deben usar las [API de REST de Outlook](https://dev.outlook.com/restapi/reference) para tener acceso al buzón del usuario.

trans-unit.source: The [Office.context.mailbox.makeEwsRequestAsync](../../reference/outlook/Office.context.mailbox.md) method is not supported in Outlook Mobile.
trans-unit.target: The [Office.context.mailbox.makeEwsRequestAsync](../../reference/outlook/Office.context.mailbox.md) method is not supported in Outlook Mobile.

trans-unit.source: Add-ins should prefer to get information from the Office.js API when possible.
trans-unit.target: Add-ins should prefer to get information from the Office.js API when possible.

trans-unit.source: If add-ins require information not exposed by the Office.js API, then they should use the [Outlook REST APIs](https://dev.outlook.com/restapi/reference) to access the user's mailbox.
trans-unit.target: If add-ins require information not exposed by the Office.js API, then they should use the [Outlook REST APIs](https://dev.outlook.com/restapi/reference) to access the user's mailbox.

trans-unit.source: Mailbox requirement set 1.5 introduces a new version of [Office.context.mailbox.getCallbackTokenAsync](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.mailbox.html#getCallbackTokenAsync) that can request an access token compatible with the REST APIs, and a new [Office.context.mailbox.restUrl](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.mailbox.html#restUrl) property that can be used to find the REST API endpoint for the user.
trans-unit.target: El conjunto de requisitos del buzón 1.5 presenta una versión nueva de [Office.context.mailbox.getCallbackTokenAsync](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.mailbox.html#getCallbackTokenAsync) que puede solicitar un token de acceso compatible con las API de REST, y una nueva propiedad [Office.context.mailbox.restUrl](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.mailbox.html#restUrl) que puede usarse para buscar el punto de conexión de la API de REST para el usuario.

trans-unit.source: Pinch zoom
trans-unit.target: Gesto de acercamiento

trans-unit.source: By default users can use the "pinch zoom" gesture to zoom in on taskpanes. If this does not make sense for your scenario, be sure to disable pinch zoom in your HTML.
trans-unit.target: De manera predeterminada, los usuarios pueden usar el "gesto de acercamiento" para ampliar los paneles de tareas. Si esto no tiene sentido en su escenario, asegúrese de deshabilitar el gesto de acercamiento en su HTML.

trans-unit.source: By default users can use the "pinch zoom" gesture to zoom in on taskpanes.
trans-unit.target: By default users can use the "pinch zoom" gesture to zoom in on taskpanes.

trans-unit.source: If this does not make sense for your scenario, be sure to disable pinch zoom in your HTML.
trans-unit.target: If this does not make sense for your scenario, be sure to disable pinch zoom in your HTML.

trans-unit.source: Closing taskpanes
trans-unit.target: Cerrar paneles de tareas

trans-unit.source: In Outlook Mobile, taskpanes take up the entire screen and by default require the user to close them to return to the message. Consider using the [Office.context.ui.closeContainer](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.ui.html#closeContainer) method to close the taskpane when your scenario is complete.
trans-unit.target: En Outlook Mobile, los paneles de tareas ocupan toda la pantalla y, de manera predeterminada, necesitan que el usuario los cierre para volver al mensaje. Considere la posibilidad de usar el método [Office.context.ui.closeContainer](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.ui.html#closeContainer) para cerrar el panel de tareas cuando el escenario esté completo.

trans-unit.source: In Outlook Mobile, taskpanes take up the entire screen and by default require the user to close them to return to the message.
trans-unit.target: In Outlook Mobile, taskpanes take up the entire screen and by default require the user to close them to return to the message.

trans-unit.source: Consider using the [Office.context.ui.closeContainer](https://dev.outlook.com/reference/add-ins/1.5/Office.context.ui.html#closeContainer) method to close the taskpane when your scenario is complete.

trans-unit.source: Compose mode and appointments
trans-unit.target: Modo de redacción y citas

trans-unit.source: Currently add-ins in Outlook Mobile only support activation when reading messages. Add-ins are not activated when composing messages or when viewing or composing appointments.
trans-unit.target: Actualmente, los complementos en Outlook Mobile solo admiten su activación al leer mensajes. Los complementos no están activados al redactar mensajes o al ver o redactar citas.

trans-unit.source: Currently add-ins in Outlook Mobile only support activation when reading messages.
trans-unit.target: Currently add-ins in Outlook Mobile only support activation when reading messages.

trans-unit.source: Add-ins are not activated when composing messages or when viewing or composing appointments.
trans-unit.target: Add-ins are not activated when composing messages or when viewing or composing appointments.
